operating
income of $1.02billion in 2007 was $113million, or 10%, lower than operating income of $1.13billion in 2006, primarily reflecting a decline in net
favorable prior year reserve development and an increase in catastrophe losses, partially offset by growth in business volume and net investment income and the $71million benefit from the new
fixed agent compensation program. net favorable prior year reserve development in 2007 and 2006 totaled $152million and $359million, respectively. catastrophe losses in 2007 totaled
