of the notes tendered their certificates in exchange for the issuance of 670,910 of the company's common shares. the remaining $857million of notes were redeemed for cash, along with accrued
interest to the date of redemption. the company recorded a $39million pretax loss ($25million after-tax) in other revenues in the second quarter of 2007 related to the
redemption, consisting of the redemption premium paid and the write-off of remaining unamortized issuance costs.
